result.text:
A Rejuvenating China and Strong China-Eritrea Strategic Partnership

On 1st of this October, the People’s Republic of China will turn 74 years old.

The Chinese nation boasts a million years of human habitation, 10,000 years of cultural history and a  civilization spanning more than 5,000 years. Throughout the long course of history, Chinese civilization, together with other civilizations of the world, has made great contributions to the evolution and progress of human civilization, in which the Chinese civilization also developed its outstanding characteristics.

Ever since the founding of the People’s  Republic of China 74 years ago, the Chinese nation has embarked on a  magnificent path towards national rejuvenation. Over the past 74 years,  under the leadership of the Communist Party of China, Chinese people of all ethnic groups have worked with one heart and one mind, accomplishing great achievements that attracted global attention, creating two miracles that are rare in the world, namely, rapid economic development and long-term social stability.

High-quality development is China’s top priority in building a modernized country in a comprehensive manner.  Since the beginning of this year, China’s economy has maintained a  rebound and upward trend, with strong resilience, great potential and  sufficient vitality, and the fundamentals of long-term improvement will not change. Looking ahead, China’s development prospects are bright and it will certainly make greater contributions to the development and progress of mankind.

The year 2023 is significant in the history of China-#Eritrea relations as it marks the 30th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between our two countries.  Just as the ancient Chinese philosopher Confucius said, a man should be steadfast at the age of thirty, the anniversary of 30 years is also important. At present, China and Eritrea have established a strategic partnership.

H.E. President Isaias Afwerki visited  China in May this year, and met with H.E. President Xi Jinping, H.E.  Premier Li Qiang and other Chinese leaders. The two heads of state have reached a series of important consensus, which ushered in a new and broad prospect for the China-Eritrea relations. Looking back at our 3  decades of diplomatic relations, there are a number of reasons behind  this good relationship:

China and Eritrea are like-minded comrades. It is frequently said by Eritrean friends that while China and  Eritrea have 30 years of diplomatic relations, the friendship between the two countries began over 60 years ago.

China and Eritrea are comrades in arms through thick and thin. China and Eritrea have always supported each other on issues regarding each others’ core interests and major concerns, and shared the same or similar views on major international issues. We both advocate fairness and justice in the international  arena, and resolutely oppose hegemony and power politics. Although China and Eritrea are geographically far apart, we treat each other with all  sincerity and share weal and woe.

China and Eritrea are partners of mutually beneficial cooperation. Our economic and trade cooperation has been developing steadily. We signed the memorandum of understanding on  “Belt and Road” cooperation. Major China-Eritrea joint-projects such as  Asmara Mining, Zara Mining, and Bisha Mining are running and thriving.  China and Eritrea have consistently conducted practical cooperation in the fields of health, agriculture, education, culture, etc. 16 batches of Chinese medical team consisting of 293 Chinese doctors have come to  Eritrea to aid the sick, and Chinese agricultural experts are implementing demonstration planting of apples, beans and oil crops in  Eritrea.

China and Eritrea are friends bonded by hearts. “The friendship of nations lies in the affinity of peoples”.  China and Eritrea enjoy a time-tested friendship and this friendship is deeply rooted in the hearts of our two peoples. The exchange between our two countries can be traced back to over a millennium. The museum in  Massawa displays an ancient Chinese ceramic wine vessel engraved with  Chinese characters “Wanhe Chanshan”, which were unearthed in Eritrea.  Two weeks ago, China’s Zhejiang Wu Opera Troupe, together with Eritrean  artists, put on two wonderful performances at Cinema Roma, receiving warm welcome from the Eritrean people.

Eritrea is known as the “Pearl of the  Red Sea”, I believe that there will be more Chinese people visiting  Eritrea in the future to appreciate Eritrea’s untouched natural scenery,  time-tested historical relics and the beauty of its harmonious diversity. Our friends from Eritrea are also most-welcome to visit  China.

In today’s world, multiple challenges and crises are intertwined. The global economic recovery remains  sluggish. The development gap is widening. Ecological environment is deteriorating. The Cold War mentality is lingering. Humanity has once again reached a crossroads of history. The Horn of Africa, where we are situated, is also confronted with a number of serious challenges.

We should embrace the idea of a  community with a shared future for mankind, promote the common values of mankind, strengthen solidarity, cooperate in good faith and work together to overcome challenges. China has put forward the Global  Development Initiative, the Global Security Initiative and the Global  Civilization Initiative, and is ready to work with all parties to promote common development and prosperity, achieve universal security  and strengthen exchanges and mutual understanding among civilizations.

Recently, China released a white paper  “A Global Community of Shared Future: China’s Proposals and Actions”,  which comprehensively introduces the concept and practice of building a  community with a shared future for mankind.

China would like to work together with  Eritrea and all other countries in pursuing the cause of building a  global community of shared future, as well as an open, inclusive, clean,  and beautiful world of lasting peace, universal security and shared  prosperity, and jointly create a better future for all of humanity.
Long live the People’s Republic of China! Long live China-Eritrea friendship!

Dai Demao
Charge d’Affaires of the
People’s Republic of China to
the State of Eritrea
